Since then, the ozone layer has partially recovered.
Yet evidence has recently emerged that U.S. companies are also releasing ozone-depleting chemicals.
While the ozone layer is rebounding overall, scientists have observed decreasing levels of the gas in certain areas.
The chemical pollution, some of which is coming from the U.S., EPA records show, has already delayed progress on the ozone layer.
Loopholes and Untracked Emissions Both the Clean Air Act and the Montreal Protocol do regulate some of these short-lived chemicals that erode the ozone layer.